ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Lab meeting in social psychology. Research ideas and ongoing studies done in John Barghes Lab are discussed.It is very much a lab meeting. Interesting for those who are interested in John Barghes research.
I would recommend it to another interested in Prof. Bargh's area of interest.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It is good to see other students research projects and learn what goes right and what goes wrong in their work. A lot of it can be useful for ones own research projects.
The course added to my knowledge in the area of social cognition, unconscious processes. Undoubtedly valuable to anyone in the field of psychology.
